<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2265&amp;p=18882#p18882</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2265&amp;p=18882#p18882"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Slalom]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2265&amp;p=18882#p18882"><![CDATA[
My emulator renders complete scanlines only and still handles Slalom correctly. The time that it renders a scanline is key: currently I do this 60 PPU clocks from the beginning of a line. It uses the catch-up method, so other aspects of PPU emulation are precise, like the time of H-blank. It's definitely a workable method.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Oct 27, 2006 12:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
